<paragraph id="FC49F4D4D00E44BCCF1CCDC26A951EE7" pageId="23" pageNumber="118">
Depending on the locality, adults of Caribbean 
<taxonomicName id="B3BE8135E28816FD3731F5528E195B40" class="Actinopterygii" family="Opistognathidae" genus="Opistognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opistognathus aurifrons" order="Perciformes" pageId="23" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aurifrons">Opistognathus aurifrons</taxonomicName>
may have relatively short or long pelvic fins, color patterns not found in Brazilian populations or that duplicate them.
</paragraph>
